image_analysis.description: A photograph showing a stairwell landing. The stairs have a blue metal railing with a wooden handrail. On the wall of the landing, two red fire extinguishers are mounted. Above the fire extinguishers is a small black sign with white text that reads '4TH FLOOR'. To the right, there is a framed document or map hanging on the wall. The floor is carpeted in a dark grey patterned material. A light fixture is visible at the top of the frame.
image_analysis.layout: Vertical composition showing a staircase leading up to a landing.

notes: The image is a standard evidentiary photograph, likely part of a site inspection or investigation. The text 'EFTA00001100' is a Bates stamp used for document tracking.
